paragraph = "Being human makes us susceptible to the onset of feelings The role of these emotions varies Some of them\n" \
            " are useful while others may be harmful The use of social media for self-expression has reached a point \n" \
            "that it makes us feel we can say anything This begins when we see people expressing anything and \n" \
            "everything that come to mind When we see everyone else voicing their likes and dislikes their \n" \
            "irritations and desires we tend to imitate what they do And because many engage in this we think that\n" \
            " it is normal and healthy However when we get used to unbridled self-expression we come to believe\n" \
            " that all feelings are valid We become convinced that in real life we should also act on our emotions \n" \
            "and our impulses Using social media this way erodes our ability to regulate our actions and reactions\n" \
            " To illustrate when something small irritates us we think that it's okay to feel this way But isn't\n" \
            " it better to foster one's patience and resilience instead of immediately complaining Or when we develop\n" \
            " an attraction to someone despite that person being in a relationship and because social media has \n" \
            "conditioned us that all feelings can be expressed we tend to think that acting on this attraction is\n" \
            " okay Not all feelings deserve expression We find ourselves creating our own problems when we let our\n" \
            " present emotions control our actions"
